All 6 tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:

**Bug:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

**Root cause:** The loop condition was `i < items.length - 1`, which stops one iteration early, skipping the last element.

```ts
// Before (buggy)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

For an array of length `n`, the original condition only reached index `n-2`, leaving the last item (index `n-1`) unprocessed. Removing the `- 1` ensures the loop runs through all elements.

